The claim with the title 'Will some money generated by Foxconn leave Wisconsin? ' says As construction crews prepare to break ground on the planned Foxconn manufacturing plant in Mount Pleasant, some in the political arena are questioning where money from the multi-billion dollar project will go. In a march 23 press release, Wisconsin Democratic gubernatorial candidate Matt Flynn said, “ taxpayer dollars will go to out-of-state businesses when they should go to Wisconsin ones. ”His comments came after Flynn learned that the lead contractors directing construction of the $10 billion LCD manufacturing plant are, in fact, out-of-state companies. Annika Dale, a Flynn campaign staffer, cited a BizTimes article as Flynn’s source. 
